    "uses": "Rivaroxaban is primarily used for the prevention and treatment of various thromboembolic disorders. It is often prescribed to prevent strokes in patients with non-valvular atrial fibrillation, as it provides a convenient alternative to warfarin with less regular monitoring required. Additionally, Rivaroxaban is indicated for the treatment and prevention of DVT and pulmonary embolism, especially after surgeries such as hip or knee replacement, where the risk of clot formation is increased. Furthermore, it may be used in patients with acute coronary syndrome to reduce the risk of major cardiovascular events.\n\nThrough its effective anticoagulant properties, Rivaroxaban improves patient outcomes and can be an important aspect of managing patients with a high risk of thromboembolic events, allowing them to maintain a better quality of life while on treatment.",
    
